### Summary

The modifications are necessary to improve the robustness and security of the code by ensuring proper error handling and initialization. This helps prevent vulnerabilities like buffer overflows, which can lead to crashes or arbitrary code execution. By implementing these changes, the code becomes safer and more resilient against malicious inputs or server responses.

